16 (1) Ten percent for all taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2006, and prior to
17 January 1, 2007;
18 (2) Twenty percent for all taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2007, and prior
19 to January 1, 2008; and
20 (3) Thirty percent for all taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2008, and prior
21 to January 1, 2025; and
22 (4) One-hundred percent for all taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2025.
23 (b) In no event shall the total amount of the tax credit under this Code section for a taxable
24 year exceed the taxpayer's income tax liability. Any unused tax credit shall not be allowed
25 to be carried forward to apply to the taxpayer's succeeding years' tax liability. No such tax
26 credit shall be allowed the taxpayer against prior years' tax liability.
27 (b.1) Notwithstanding the provisions of subsection (b) of this Code section, for taxable
28 years beginning on or after January 1, 2025, if the total amount of the tax credit provided
29 for in this Code section exceeds the taxpayer's income tax liability for a taxable year, such
30 excess funds shall be refunded to the taxpayer.
31 (c) The commissioner shall be authorized to promulgate any rules and regulations
32 necessary to implement and administer this Code section."
33 SECTION 2.
34 This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2025, and shall be applicable to all taxable years
35 beginning on or after January 1, 2025.
36 SECTION 3.
37 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
